title: LiquidSonics Filtrate v1.111 WiN MacOSX-R2R [deepstatus]
description:
LiquidSonics Filtrate v1.111 WiN MacOSX







LiquidSonics Filtrate is an efficient linear phase 8-band stereo parametric audio equaliser for Mac and PC.


Features and Specifications:

   Linear phase equaliser
   8 independent left, right, or stereo bands
   MIDI key frequency control for each band (-12 to 24 semitone offset)
   MIDI CC control of cutoff, gain and Q for all bands
   Filter mix control for EQ mix fading
   Mac and PC supported (VST / RTAS / AU)
   64-bit VST and AU on Mac and PC
   CUDA support on PC







System Requirements

   Windows XP, Vista, 7 or 8
   Intel Mac - Leopard to Mavericks (OS X 10.5.8 - 10.9.x)
   RTAS, VST 2.4 (PC and Mac) and AU host (Mac only)
   Pentium 4 and above recommended
   64-bit VST/AU versions require a 64-bit capable host





      [Installation]

     

[WiN]
1.Install the software as demo version.
2.Patch the plugins.
3.Enjoy!

[CleanUp]
If you have installed fake licenses before, you should wipe the old data.
Delete following regkey and install again.
This will also reset the trial date.

HKEY_CURRENT_USERSoftwareLiquidSonics
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESOFTWARELiquidSonics
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESOFTWARELSPersistent

64bitOS
HKEY_CURRENT_USERSoftwareLiquidSonics
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESOFTWARELiquidSonics
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESOFTWARELSPersistent
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESoftwareWOW6432NodeLiquidSonics
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESoftwareWOW6432NodeLSPersistent
           


[MacOSX]
1.Uninstall previous versions.
2.Clean up (see below).
3.Install the software.
4.Copy our cracks.
 If you choose AU(ALT), copy our *.vst to /*.component/ instead.
 Default AU is native but AU(ALT) is a VST wrapper.
5.Enjoy!

[CleanUp]
If you have installed previous version, delete the following directory :
/User/Library/Preferences/LiquidSonics
